    • build

      public GameControllerState build​(int workerRow, int workerColumn, int buildRow, int buildColumn, Model gd) throws DivinityPowerException, MaximumLevelReachedException, OccupiedCellException, NotAdjacentCellException, DomedCellException
      Redefined since it has to check if we are trying to perform the second build on cells different from the first. If the player build a third level, return a turn change since he can't complete a second build.
      Overrides:
      build in class Divinity
      Parameters:
      workerRow - the row where the worker is
      workerColumn - the column where the worker is
      buildRow - the row where the player wants to add a level
      buildColumn - the column where the player wants to add a level
      gd - the game status
      Returns:
      the next action of the controller
      Throws:
      NotAdjacentCellException - if the cell where the player wants to build is not adiacent to the worker's one
      OccupiedCellException - if the destination cell is occupied by another worker
      DomedCellException - is the cell is already domed
      MaximumLevelReachedException - if the cell contains a level 3 building
      DivinityPowerException - if another divinity blocks the increment of the level

    • dome

      public GameControllerState dome​(int workerRow, int workerColumn, int domeRow, int domeColumn, Model gd) throws NotAdjacentCellException, OccupiedCellException, DomedCellException, MaximumLevelNotReachedException, DivinityPowerException
      Requires the model to register a dome operation performed by the player
      Overrides:
      dome in class Divinity
      Parameters:
      workerRow - the row where the worker is
      workerColumn - the column where the worker is
      domeRow - the row where the player wants to add the dome
      domeColumn - the column where the player wants to add the dome
      gd - the current game board state
      Returns:
      the next controller FSM state
      Throws:
      NotAdjacentCellException - if player is trying to put a dome on a cell not adjacent to the worker
      OccupiedCellException - if player is trying to put a dome on a occupied cell
      DomedCellException - if player is trying to put a dome on an already domed cell
      MaximumLevelNotReachedException - if the player is trying to put a dome on a cell with level lower than 2
      DivinityPowerException - if another divinity blocks the dome, or if the player is trying to put a dome as second operation.
